Popeye is just about to have lunch when Olive comes knocking at his door talking about some strange problem that she has been having. It is just a matter of time before he realizes that he won't be able to eat in peace so he decides to solve her problem first. The problem for Popeye is to find whether the number given to him by Olive can be expressed as a sum of the cubes of any two numbers i, j or not where i ≥ 0, j ≥ 0.

Input
First line of input contains t, the number of test cases. The next 't' lines contain n, the number that is given to Popeye by Olive.
0
0

Output
Output would be a single number, that would be the number of values given to Popeye that can be expressed as a sum of two cubes.

Example

Input:
5
40
35
53
65
27

Output:
3
